  "bookTitle": "Elven Knight (Alt)",
  "bookId": 69,
  "firstAcquaintance": "The saint wanted to fight too, so Mu Renier transformed into a bunny girl.",
  "personality": "The comfort of the bunny girl outfit shocked her, making her more proactive about engaging with civilization outside the forest. She hasn't forgotten her duties as a saint, staying true to herself and maintaining her usual calm demeanor.",
  "like": "Golden candy, drinking alcohol",
  "familiarData": "Mu Renier is the elven saint, but the saint's power is to maintain the forest's life force, and she has no combat ability herself. She cannot even use the bow and arrow that elves are skilled with.\nIn her powerlessness, she received power from another dimension, unleashing another form of the saint's garment -- the Divine Bunny Girl.\nThe liberated holy garment can reshape itself, and a saint with enough talent can manipulate the garment to transform into various shapes for combat.\nHowever, the prototype of the \"Divine Bunny Girl\" was created by absorbing others' magical power, and deviations in understanding the garment's functions led to creating an outfit she was unaccustomed to, causing some minor troubles.\n\n\"So what's the minor trouble? I don't see any.\"\n\"Don't ask.\"\nSetting aside the minor troubles, she herself quite likes the bunny girl outfit. Rabbits are a feature of the forest, and the close-fitting thin stockings do not hinder her sensitivity to nature's magical power, and she can use the holy garment's power to enhance her physical abilities.\nThe bunny girl outfit showed Mu Renier the good side of civilization that suits the forest, which made her more willing to try things from the outside world, and from that she discovered her own mission as a saint.",
